3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the challenges of controlling soft materials and the use of tensegrity structures for stability, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): The paper discusses the design and construction of the soft robot, which falls under the domain of mechanical engineering. 
5. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): Soft robotics is an emerging field that seeks to harness the properties of soft materials for creating resilient machines, which falls under the domain of emerging technologies.
